President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Alabama due to the impact of Hurricane Isaac. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected area. The declaration allows for federal funding to be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Joe M. Girot has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area. Additional designations may be made if requested by the state and further damage assessments warrant it. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.